Named after former [[National Union of Teachers]] (NUT) General Secretary [[Fred Jarvis]] and his late wife, the '''Fred and Anne Jarvis Award''' was established in 2007 and first awarded in 2008. It is presented annually by the NUT, originally to individuals outside the NUT who campaign on education and related issues but in 2017 the award was made to an NUT member.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.eriding.net/resources/sis/edpub/071001_rwilliams_sis_edpub_281.pdf | title=Memorial for Anne Jarvis at the Institute of Education | publisher=Education Publishing Worldwide Limited | date=21 September 2007 | accessdate=21 November 2012 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502013620/http://www.eriding.net/resources/sis/edpub/071001_rwilliams_sis_edpub_281.pdf | archivedate=2 May 2014 | df= }}</ref>
