{{Infobox person |name=Pierre Koukjian |image= |caption=Pierre Koukjian }}
'''Pierre Koukjian''' (born 1962 in [[Beirut]]) is an artist based in [[Geneva]], [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thinkphuket.com/phuket-art-scene/1498-pierre-koukjian-artist|title=Pierre Koukjian|work=Think Phuket|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author = Usnisa Sukhsvasti| title =Indigo pearl shows an eclectic| quote =The courtyard was bordered with large canvases by award-winning Lebanese designer and artist Pierre Koukjian. Growing up in Germany, France and the Middle East, Koukjian came to the arts through jewellery.| newspaper =[[Bangkok Post]]|date =April 28, 2013| url =http://www.bangkokpost.com/lifestyle/art/347385/indigo-pearl-shows-an-eclectic| accessdate = 12 August 2015}}</ref> His life work focuses mainly on [[contemporary art]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-e-art.com/artists/pierre-koukjian/|title=Pierre Koukjian|work=m-e-art.com|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author =| title =Art Dubai 2012: Where the Middle East came to scream| quote = Lebanese artist Pierre Koukjian crafted words in bright neon lights as they flash on and off to depict a prolonged electricity problem in his home country.| newspaper =[[Al Arabiya]]| date =March 25, 2012| url =http://www.alarabiya.net/articles/2012/03/25/203009.html| accessdate = 12 August 2015}}</ref> and [[watch]] design.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.watchonista.com/2914/watchonista-blog/news/pierre-koukjian-has-quit-delacour-and-created-hedera|title=Pierre Koukjian has quit deLaCour and created HEDERA|date=14 July 2015|work=Watchonista|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref> His work can be found at the Musee de l'Horlogerie Geneve.<ref name="watchonista">{{cite web|url=http://www.watchonista.com/2914/watchonista-blog/news/delacour-bichrono-offered-musee-d%E2%80%99horlogerie-de-geneve|title=A deLaCour Bichrono offered to the Musée d’Horlogerie de Genève - Watchonista|publisher=watchonista.com|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref> His contemporary art ranges from [[Oil painting|oil]] on canvas to metal stainless steel sculptures and have been denoted as [[postmodernist]] by critics.<ref name="petriepr">{{cite web|url=http://petriepr.com/rivet-the-culinary-theatre-at-rivet-at-indigo-pearl/|title=Rivet - The Culinary Theatre at Indigo Pearl &bull; Petrie PR|publisher=petriepr.com|accessdate=12 August 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303232404/http://petriepr.com/rivet-the-culinary-theatre-at-rivet-at-indigo-pearl/|archivedate=3 March 2016|df=}}</ref>
==Watchmaking== Pierre Koukjian has pioneered many advancements in the Swiss watchmaking industry. He later added to his creations various world premiere creations such as the double repeater and inlaying a tobacco leaf in the dial of a watch.<ref name="frostoflondon">{{cite web|url=http://www.frostoflondon.co.uk/about-delacour-i43|title=About deLaCour|publisher=frostoflondon.co.uk|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref>
==Contemporary art== Pierre Koukjian's work in art were born from a need to explore new materials and way of expressing oneself on an art medium. He is mostly known for his critiques of Lebanese society with his neon piece "Electricity ON, Electricity OFF". A recent polemic in the contemporary art world has put Pierre KOUKJIAN as the eye witness of the destruction of a painting during a Sotheby's auction where the artist said"a turning point in the history of contemporary and conceptual art." <ref>https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2018/10/06/world/europe/ap-eu-britain-bansky.html</ref> The timing, nature of his work, and enthusiasm about the whole situation has led to suspicions of KOUKJIAN being in fact the original Banksy. <ref>https://medium.com/@stephanielord_66044/is-koukjian-banksy-drawing-the-parallels-6922e39e0b96</ref>
==Awards and notable works==
[[File:Pierre Koukjian at fight aids Monaco.jpg|thumb|Pierre Koukjian in company of prince and princess Albert and Stephanie de Monaco at the charity gala "fight aids Monaco 2017"]]
Pierre Koukjian has won multiple awards for his work, amongst them the Tokyo "Unique design" award<ref name="europastar">{{cite web|url=http://www.europastar.com/news/1000744304-delacour-and-fran-x00e7-ois-paul-journe-win.html|title=deLaCour and Fran&#x00E7;ois Paul Journe win awards|publisher=europastar.com|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref> and the second best design in the Grand Prix d'Horlogerie in Geneva, 2003.<ref name="europastar2">{{cite web|url=http://www.europastar.com/magazine/highlights/1000479106-delacour-making-it-big-with-outsize.html|title=deLaCour - Making it big with ‘OUTSIZE’|publisher=europastar.com|accessdate=12 August 2015}}</ref>
The sculpture "Haricot magique" is a public work exhibited at the roundabout of Cologny in Geneva, Switzerland.<ref>http://www.cologny.ch/pierre-koukjian-haricot-magique</ref>
The watch "Bichrono" is exhibited at the museum "Musée d'art et d'histoire" in Geneva, Switzerland.<ref>http://institutions.ville-geneve.ch/fr/mah/collections-publications/collections/dons-acquisitions/2013/</ref>
The artist's recent work "Mass grave" depicting a used condom made of blown glass was chosen by the Princess Stephanie de Monaco to be part of the auction "Fight aids Monaco" where the proceedings would go to help the fight against aids.<ref>http://www.fightaidsmonaco.com/wp-content/uploads/CATALOGUE-2017-Web-1.pdf</ref>
